key goals of the game include:
	it should be hard to conquer the world
	it should not be very hard to defend what is under your control
	there is no player order - all players play their turns independently of each other (both on the map and in battles); they don't see the actions of others before the end of their own turn
	computer players have as much information as local (manual) players; no handicap is used to make computers look stronger
	computers value unit strength and don't hardcode it; unit stats can change and computers will still play as adequately

desired effects:
	slow to make all regions produce powerful units
	expensive to have huge armies
	it's reasonable to develop some regions and not develop others

future goals:
	war should not be the core part of the gameplay; diplomacy, economy, trade, etc. should also play a part

