----

simple economy

each region has a given population; part of it supports the city; the others can be ordered to collect resources
wood, stone, iron and gold require special buildings to be produced
there are buildings that allow producing resources more efficiently (e.g. irrigation)
gold comes from taxes; the population that is not busy collecting resources does not require payment (and results in gold income)
from the free population one can set the proportion that will collect each of the resources (food, stone, wood, iron); the income is not proportional to the number of people

