	+1 food
? watermill
	+1 food
? tillage
	food +2
drift mine (requires: mine)
	stone +2
gold mine (requires mine)
	+1 gold

foundry



region-specific characteristics
	water (required for watermill, irrigation, moat, etc.)
	wood (required for sawmill)
	ore (required for mine)
	gold (required for gold mine)

gold comes from taxes (depending on the population)




technologies:
    conservatory
    drainage / sewage
	tillage
	crop rotation

http://www.euratlas.net/history/europe/1/entity_15233.html

----

trading

constructions involved: marketplace, roads, port

trading benefits are determined by population of the region and its neighbors
roads increase the benefits from land neighbors
port increases the benefits from sea neighbors (? whatever that means)

----

units that attack while moving (applicable in many games)

----

battering ram - makes assault conceivable; useful because it can hardly be destroyed by shooters
balista - makes troops inside garrison vulnerable (which often means they have to attack)
ditch - slows down movement
moat - makes battering ram mostly useless
